PortSystem          1.0

name                xcode-copilot-server
version             3.4.0
revision            0

categories          devel
license             MIT
maintainers         {@eejd} openmaintainer

description         GitHub Copilot proxy server for Xcode's AI coding features

long_description    ${name} is a proxy API server that lets you use GitHub \
                    Copilot as an LLM provider in Xcode. It wraps the GitHub \
                    Copilot SDK and exposes it as an OpenAI-compatible, \
                    Anthropic-compatible, or OpenAI Responses-compatible API \
                    on localhost, allowing Xcode to use Copilot as a custom \
                    model provider or as the backend for Claude Agent and \
                    Codex Agent. Supports launchd socket activation for \
                    on-demand background operation.

homepage            https://github.com/theblixguy/xcode-copilot-server

master_sites        https://registry.npmjs.org/${name}/-/

distname            ${name}-${version}
extract.suffix      .tgz

checksums           rmd160  a92e4e4fff874905babcb99c3622e7c8486453fa \
                    sha256  152b617cd329c73f0a930d85a1ece5137aa000940d62caa8448d997b0bdf3f20 \
                    size    76019

worksrcdir          package

# Upstream requires Node.js >= 25.6.0 (see .node-version and package.json
# engines field). nodejs24 is the closest currently available in MacPorts;
# update this dependency to nodejs25 once that port is available.
depends_lib         path:bin/node:nodejs24
depends_build       path:bin/npm:npm11

use_configure       no

build {
    # Install only production (runtime) dependencies.
    # This also triggers koffi's postinstall to download its prebuilt native
    # binary for the current platform.
    system -W ${worksrcpath} "${prefix}/bin/npm install --omit=dev"
}

post-build {
    # Replace the generic env-based shebang with the MacPorts node path so
    # the script uses the port's Node.js installation at runtime.
    reinplace "s|#!/usr/bin/env node|#!${prefix}/bin/node|" \
        ${worksrcpath}/dist/index.js
}

destroot {
    set nm_dir ${destroot}${prefix}/lib/node_modules

    # Create node_modules directory and copy the package tree (dist/, scripts/,
    # config.json5, package.json, and installed node_modules/) into it.
    xinstall -d ${nm_dir}
    file copy ${worksrcpath} ${nm_dir}/${name}

    # Ensure the main entry-point is executable.
    file attributes ${nm_dir}/${name}/dist/index.js -permissions 0755

    # Expose the binary via the standard MacPorts bin directory.
    ln -s ${prefix}/lib/node_modules/${name}/dist/index.js \
        ${destroot}${prefix}/bin/${name}
}

notes "
=== Authentication ===

${name} requires a GitHub Copilot subscription. You must authenticate
before starting the server. Choose one of the following methods:

RECOMMENDED — GitHub CLI (port:gh):

  sudo port install gh
  gh auth login

  This stores a token in the macOS Keychain and is the most seamless option.
  It also works automatically when the server is installed as a launchd agent.

ALTERNATIVE — Environment variable:

  Create a GitHub personal access token at https://github.com/settings/tokens
  with Copilot access (classic PAT: no special scope needed beyond your
  Copilot subscription; fine-grained PAT: enable GitHub Copilot permission).
  Then export it in your shell startup file:

    export GITHUB_TOKEN=your_token_here

  For the launchd agent, set it before installing:

    launchctl setenv GITHUB_TOKEN your_token_here
    ${name} install-agent

  NOTE: If you export GITHUB_TOKEN, it will be embedded in the agent plist
  at ~/Library/LaunchAgents/. Set appropriate file permissions if concerned.

NOTE — VS Code Copilot credentials are NOT shared:
  Even if you are already authenticated with GitHub Copilot in VS Code,
  ${name} cannot access those credentials (VS Code stores them in its own
  private Keychain entries). You must authenticate separately using one of
  the methods above.

=== Usage ===

Start the server (registers all providers, auto mode):
  ${name}

Start a single provider:
  ${name} --proxy openai    # Custom model provider
  ${name} --proxy claude    # Claude Agent backend
  ${name} --proxy codex     # Codex Agent backend

Install as a launchd agent (starts automatically on demand):
  ${name} install-agent

Uninstall the launchd agent:
  ${name} uninstall-agent

See '${name} --help' for the full CLI reference.

=== Node.js version note ===

Upstream requires Node.js >= 25.6.0. This port uses nodejs24, which is
the closest version currently available in MacPorts. The server should
work correctly; the EBADENGINE warning from npm during install is expected
and harmless. Update this port's dependency to nodejs25 once that port
becomes available in MacPorts.
"

livecheck.type      regex
